The paper deals with algorithms for constructing coresets for two well-studied problems in computational geometry and machine learning: subspace approximation and k-median. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are both likely categories. The algorithms presented in the paper involve linear algebraic operations and optimization techniques, which are common in numerical analysis and scientific computing, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible category as well. The paper also discusses the size and running time of the coresets, which are related to data structures and algorithmic efficiency, respectively, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as additional possible categories.
